## 解説

`sort` は既定で昇順に並べ替えます。出力は値の間だけに空白を入れます。

```cpp
sort(v.begin(), v.end());
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { if (i) cout << " "; cout << v[i]; }
cout << "\n";
```

answer_code:
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> v(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> v[i];
    sort(v.begin(), v.end());
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { if (i) cout << " "; cout << v[i]; }
    cout << "\n";
    return 0;
}
